#mobile_app

Task: Refine the Game Details / Analytics screen to be more compact and reduce vertical spacing.

Context:
The current design spreads information too much and uses oversized metric cards. The new design should prioritize density and readability while maintaining the existing visual style.

Changes:

Preview Section

Remove the "Vista previa" title and container card.

Instead display the game photos directly below the game title as a horizontal row of thumbnails.

Example layout:

Game title
Row of photo thumbnails

Thumbnails:
- rounded corners
- square aspect ratio
- evenly spaced
- scrollable horizontally if needed

Metrics Section

Keep all 5 metrics but compress them into a compact grid.

Remove metric icons.

Metrics to display:
- Jugadas
- Usuarios únicos
- Tasa de finalización
- Intentos promedio
- Tiempo promedio

Layout:

2-column grid for the first 4 metrics
Final metric spans full width.

Example:

Jugadas            Usuarios únicos
247                89

Tasa de finalización   Intentos promedio
73%                    18

Tiempo promedio
2:34

Metric cards should:
- have reduced padding
- emphasize the numeric value
- remove large icons

Leaderboard Section

Add a "Leaderboard" section showing the top 3 players.

Each row includes:
Rank medal icon
Player name
Attempts
Completion time

Example:

🥇 Ana      8 intentos   0:41
🥈 Marcos   9 intentos   0:52
🥉 Laura   10 intentos   1:02

Add a link below:

"Ver leaderboard completo"

Recent Plays

Rename section to:

"Últimas partidas"

Show only the two most recent entries.

Example row:

5 mar — 16 intentos • 2:15

Add link:

"Ver todas"

Share Section

Keep existing buttons:

Primary button:
"Compartir juego"

Secondary button:
"Copiar enlace"

Constraints:

- Reduce vertical spacing between sections
- Keep the screen scannable
- Avoid oversized cards
- Maintain visual consistency with the rest of the app
- Mobile-first layout